Subhasist Forward Bloc is a political party in Tamil Nadu, India. The party was founded in 1963 by Sasivarna Thevar, after a power vacuum led Thevar to try to take control of the All India Forward Bloc (AFIB party in Tamil Nadu. When he failed, he quit to launch the Subhasist Forward Bloc party, a splinter-group of the AIFB.[1] The party is mainly concentrated in Southern India, in the states of Tamil Nadu and Karnataka. The general secretary of the party is K. Kandasamy.
